## Tor Instance 1 Configuration

##### Cover up your tor traffic with obfs4 bridges #####
# Obfs4 Bridge Configuration from 20.01.2026, you can get fresh ones from https://bridges.torproject.org/

# Basic settings
SocksPort 127.0.0.1:9050
DataDirectory /var/lib/tor1
Log notice file /var/log/tor/tor1.log

# Control port (optional, for monitoring)
#ControlPort 9151
#CookieAuthentication 1

# Performance tuning
NumEntryGuards 3
MaxCircuitDirtiness 600
NewCircuitPeriod 30
CircuitBuildTimeout 60

# Stream isolation (anti-timing attack)
#SocksPort 127.0.0.1:9050 IsolateDestAddr 1 IsolateDestPort 1
#SocksPort 9050 SessionGroup=1

# DNS through Tor


# Disable client-side exit node caching
#UseEntryGuards 1

# Bandwidth
RelayBandwidthRate 0
RelayBandwidthBurst 0

# Disable running as relay/exit
ORPort 0
DirPort 0
ExitPolicy reject *:*
ExitRelay 0
# Security enhancements
#ExitNodes {NG},{HK},{BR},{JP},{IN},{ID},{KR},{SC},{ZA},{PE}

### If using a bridge, EntryNodes are not needed nor tor will run #####
#EntryNodes {NG},{HK},{BR},{JP},{IN},{ID},{KR},{SC}

